{"id":14881517,"mediaExerciseId":"36103d2e-1ca7-47c6-b339-99bd621de1dc","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":612404,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":531,"solutions":[{"id":6030669,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the number of shares needed to be sold. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let us first identify the given amounts in the problem: \n\n\n| | Amount$\\hspace{5pt}$| \n|:--|--:| \n|Amount of funds needed to be raised | $60 million |\n|Offer price  | $21.00 | \n|Spread  |7%|\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let us determine the required amount of the proceeds from sales. As we have seen in the problem, the company has to raise funds amounting to $60 million. Hence, the flotation cost from this amount is deducted. We will use this information to determine the sales proceeds. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Amount of funds to raise }&={\\text{S $\\times$ (1 - FC)}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$ \n\nWhere: \n\nS = Sales proceeds \n\nFC = Flotation costs","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":60,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/8ced125fc55bc77dc41fbd43fe881699/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/8ced125fc55bc77dc41fbd43fe881699/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"We will use the formula from step 3 to compute the sales proceeds. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{\\$60 million }&={\\text{S $\\times$ (1 - 7\\%)}}\\\\[5pt]\n\\text{\\$60 million }&={\\text{S $\\times$ 0.93}}\\\\[5pt]\n\\text{\\$60 million }&={\\text{0.93S}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$ ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/4f74a437794ed015c50bc96df4ff08ed/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":54,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/4f74a437794ed015c50bc96df4ff08ed/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Then, let us divide both sides by 0.93 to cancel out the coefficient of S. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\dfrac{\\text{0.93S}}{{0.93}}&=\\dfrac{\\text{\\$60 million}}{\\text{0.93}}\\\\[10pt]\n{\\text{S}}&={\\textbf{\\$64,516,129.03}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$ \n\n**The company's sales proceeds needed from the sale of stocks amounts to $64,516,129.03.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"We can now compute the number of shares needed to be sold. This is computed by dividing the sales proceeds by the offer price. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n{\\text{Number of shares }}&=\\dfrac{\\text{Sales proceed}}{\\text{Offer price}}\\\\[10pt]\n&=\\dfrac{\\text{\\$64,516,129.03}}{\\text{\\$21.00}}\\\\[10pt]\n&={\\textbf{3,072,197}}\n\\end{aligned}$$ \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":219,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/a0befd73a01e9ee4f909754ed90f4ef0/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":111,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/177f4d1f7bedfbd84df255802cadf383/a0befd73a01e9ee4f909754ed90f4ef0/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**To conclude, the number of shares needed to be sold is 3,072,197.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3748cdca-9c2e-4cb5-ad03-ead3708b7a9d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881518,"exerciseName":"6","page":532,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"56b0baa1-443e-429c-a0d9-1082d735f0eb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-questions-and-problems-6-56b0baa1-443e-429c-a0d9-1082d735f0eb"},{"id":14881519,"exerciseName":"7","page":532,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"cfe19226-fffe-4aa5-a6fc-cf6d3b1e4641","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-questions-and-problems-7-cfe19226-fffe-4aa5-a6fc-cf6d3b1e4641"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881516,"exerciseName":"4","page":531,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e252b584-bc00-43bc-aa64-a9753c5c3da3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-quest